Fix devcontainer login shell; use debian:testing

`rumpel enter` execs the container user's passwd login shell.  The
.devcontainer user was created without an explicit `-s`, so on Debian
it defaulted to /bin/sh (dash), dropping the user onto a bare `$`
prompt instead of bash.  Set the user's shell to /bin/bash via usermod
so it is normalized whether the user is freshly created or inherited
from the base image.

Also bump the default base image from debian:trixie to debian:testing.
